Agent Development Kit (ADK) – Full Notes
Agent Development Kit (ADK) is Google’s framework for building intelligent AI agents that can reason, remember
context, and take real-world actions using Large Language Models (LLMs).
Why ADK?
Unlike traditional chatbots, ADK agents are autonomous systems capable of planning tasks, calling tools, handling
memory, and interacting with external services securely.
ADK High-Level Architecture
User
ADK Agent
LLM (Reasoning Engine)
Planner
Tools / APIs (DB, Web, Email)
Core Components of ADK- Agent: Controls interaction, reasoning, and execution flow.- LLM: Performs natural language understanding and reasoning.- Planner: Breaks complex goals into executable steps.- Tools: APIs and services used to perform actions.- Memory: Stores short-term and long-term context.
Real-World Use Cases- Healthcare bots for appointments and symptom analysis- E-commerce assistants for product and order handling- HR automation for payroll and leave management- IVR and voice automation systems
Important Interview Questions- What is ADK and how does it work?- How is an AI agent different from a chatbot?- What is tool calling in ADK?- Explain multi-agent systems.
Summary: ADK enables enterprise-grade AI agents that can reason, remember, and act autonomously by
combining LLMs, tools, and memory
